info.narration:
[
{Inside of $0’s unit, a suffocating silence draws near.},
{The stillness that encroaches upon the room is broken by the horrible creaking of the rocking chair.},
{$0’s rocking chair, which stands atop an unnaturally mold-covered floor, creaks.},
{Being unable to bear the stories $0 recounts, the floor and walls of the Containment Unit have cracked here and there.}
]

[
{An old curse permeates $0’s tales.},
{$0’s soul faded away in solitude long ago.},
{Her numerous stories once fascinated people, but after a long time, a curse has seeped into her tales.},
{Her stories are poisonous things. They infiltrate all those who surround and listen, leading them into an unbearable world.}
]

[
{$0 is deaf and nearly blind, yet she still recognizes the presence of #0.},
{$0 doesn’t need to look at #0. They’ll look at her once she begins storytelling anyhow.},
{Conversation is meaningless to $0. All she needs is an audience… #0.}
]

[
{#0 has finished their designated work. They scamper out of $0’s Containment Unit quickly.},
{#0 leaves the unit after finishing up their work. The solitude that replaces their presence will be filled with $0’s stories.},
{Before $0’s ever-winding story began, #0 managed to finish their work quickly to get out of there safely.}
